Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @Carrots{12%ounce} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long
pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and
mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

== Panko Topping ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup},
@Hot Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, and a
pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{} (for 4 servings, spread out across
entire sheet).

Spread tops of chicken with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}. Mound with panko mixture,
pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

== Roasted Carrots ==

Toss carrots on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss carrots on a second sheet.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and carrots are browned and
tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4, roast chicken on middle rack and carrots on top
rack.)

Transfer chicken to a #plate{} to rest.

> If carrots are done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

== Garlic Scallion Couscous ==

While chicken and carrots roast, add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} to boiling water.
Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain thoroughly.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) in empty #pot{} over medium heat.
Add scallion whites and garlic; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Return cooked couscous to pot and stir until coated. Taste and season with salt and
pepper. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Once carrots are done roasting, carefully toss with lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon
juice to taste.

Divide chicken, carrots, and couscous between plates. Garnish chicken with scallion
greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.